  "intent_precise": "Omega Biotek Mag-Bind Viral RNA XPress Kit: Using magplate (deep_well_plate, slot 3), flatplate (plate, slot 5), reagent reservoir 1 (reservoir, slot 5). With magnetic module, Temperature Module Gen2 module. (1) Disengage magnets to release beads. (2) Disengage magnets to release beads. (3) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (4) Pause for manual intervention. (5) Pause: Please empty tips from waste before resuming. (6) Pause: Please empty waste (slot 11) before resuming. (7) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (8) Distribute from source A1 to destination wells A1. (9) Mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L. (10) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (11) Incubate for 2 minutes. (12) Disengage magnets to release beads. (13) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (14) Mix mix_reps times at 150\u00b5L. (15) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (16) Incubate for 5 minutes. (17) Transfer from source to destination. (18) Mix 10 times. (19) Incubate for 2 minutes. (20) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (21) Incubate for 2 minutes. (22) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (23) Transfer 240\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (24) Mix 15 times at 200\u00b5L. (25) Engage magnets at magheightmm height for bead separation. (26) Incubate for 2 minutes. (27) Incubate for 5 minutes. (28) Disengage magnets to release beads.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform distribute to A1, magnetic bead separation, temperature control (4\u00b0C). (volumes 20\u00b5L-240\u00b5L, ~19 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Omega Biotek Mag-Bind Viral RNA XPress Kit protocol, set up your magnetic module with the deep well plate in slot 3 and flat plate in slot 5, then cool the Temperature Module Gen2 to 4\u00b0C before starting. You'll need to disengage the magnets initially to release beads, then transfer samples from A1 to A1 and mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L before engaging magnets for 2-minute bead separation. Continue with alternating magnet engagement/disengagement cycles, including a 5-minute incubation step and mixing at 150\u00b5L for the specified mix_reps, followed by transfers of 40\u00b5L and 240\u00b5L to A1 with 15 times mixing at 200\u00b5L. Complete the protocol with final magnetic separation cycles including 2-minute and 5-minute incubations before releasing the beads, and remember to empty tips and waste from slot 11 when prompted.",
